text: Madison County is a county in the U.S. state of Alabama. As of the 2020 census, the population was 388,153, making it the third-most populous county in Alabama. The county seat is Huntsville. The county is named in honor of James Madison, fourth President of the United States of America. == References == Category:Alabama counties Category:1808 establishments in the United States Category:1800s establishments in Mississippi Territory
title: Madison County, Alabama
